1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,086
[Lara] <i>Why is Datu Rahman</i>
<i>targeting you in his video?</i>

2
00:00:03,169 --> 00:00:05,880
You keep saying there's a traitor in NLEA.

3
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:08,299
Tell me the truth. Are you suspecting me?

4
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:09,467
Are you hiding anything?

5
00:00:09,551 --> 00:00:11,428
- No.
- Good.

6
00:00:13,972 --> 00:00:15,056
[Malik] Why are you here?

7
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:16,224
[Jalil] <i>Datu Rahman surrendered to me.</i>

8
00:00:16,307 --> 00:00:17,892
- [Ibrahim] <i>What?</i>
- <i>[Jalil] I'm here to pick him up.</i>

9
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:19,310
[Datu Rahman] <i>I will go with them.</i>

10
00:00:19,394 --> 00:00:23,440
<i>Don't worry. He will protect me.</i>

11
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:27,318
You need to gather
Task Force Alpha right now.

12
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:28,737
[in English] What's going on?

13
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:29,988
A VIP is coming.

14
00:00:30,071 --> 00:00:32,365
[Marcus] <i>Whoever this person is,</i>
<i>his life is in danger,</i>

15
00:00:32,949 --> 00:00:34,743
<i>and we need to protect him.</i>

16
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:35,827
[in English] Something
is happening here, Dad.

17
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:37,245
And you don't know?

18
00:00:37,328 --> 00:00:40,373
[Manuel] <i>If something's happening there</i>
<i>and you have no idea,</i>

19
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:43,042
<i>then you are not doing your job well.</i>

20
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:44,544
[Lara, in English] <i>Felix,</i>
<i>you have to do something.</i>

21
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:46,337
Mustapha can't take Datu Rahman.

22
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,464
[Felix] <i>What do you want to do?</i>

23
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:49,716
<i>Kill Datu Rahman here now?</i>

24
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:51,885
How did you find Datu Rahman?

25
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:54,888
The Muslims trust me.

26
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:58,058
[Jalil] <i>Datu Rahman came with me</i>
<i>because he trusts me.</i>

27
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:01,311
Reyes, I know you hid Datu Rahman.

28
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:04,189
[Jalil] <i>I know you helped him escape</i>
<i>from Zylverix.</i>

29
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:05,190
How did you know?

30
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:07,859
[Jalil] <i>Don't worry. I won't tell anyone.</i>

31
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:09,819
It'll be our secret.

32
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:12,697
[tense music playing]

33
00:01:16,951 --> 00:01:19,204
[mysterious theme music playing]

34
00:01:32,717 --> 00:01:35,720
[pensive music playing]

35
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:12,465
- [explosion]
- [screaming]

36
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:13,716
[people screaming]

37
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:20,265
- [woman screaming]
- [young Lara] Daddy…

38
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:21,683
[crying]

39
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:24,185
[young Lara] Daddy!

40
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:30,108
What did you do?!

41
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:36,281
[stirring music playing]

42
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:53,089
[pensive music playing]

43
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,054
‪[dramatic sting]

44
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:23,036
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

45
00:03:23,828 --> 00:03:24,871
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you too.

46
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,624
[in English] Welcome, sir.

47
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,794
I'm sorry for the sudden notice.

48
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:35,089
I called you as soon
as I received word from our ranks

49
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:36,758
that Datu Rahman had surrendered.

50
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:40,470
[phone buzzing]

51
00:03:43,264 --> 00:03:44,432
Hello?

52
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,018
What?

53
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:50,605
Good.

54
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:52,690
Be careful.

55
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:56,486
Make sure he makes it here alive.

56
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,112
I'll take care of the rest.

57
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:04,911
Here is the court order you requested

58
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,704
for custody of Datu Rahman.

59
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:08,206
[pensive music playing]

60
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:13,670
I will never forget what you did.

61
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:16,089
I'll always remember it.

62
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:18,508
[pensive music playing]

63
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:25,348
Where is he?

64
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:29,477
Oh, he's secured.
He's in his holding cell.

65
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,813
[music intensifies]

66
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,946
- [in English] This way.
- [reporters clamoring]

67
00:04:40,029 --> 00:04:41,990
- [reporter 1] Sir! Sir! Sir!
- [reporter 2] Wait, sir!

68
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:44,409
[man, in English] <i>All</i>
<i>our respective nations have established</i>

69
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:46,452
<i>robust legal frameworks.</i>

70
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:48,871
<i>The operational reality of enforcement</i>

71
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:51,958
<i>is often hampered</i>
<i>by disparate customs protocols</i>

72
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,544
<i>and the sheer geographical complexity</i>

73
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:56,796
<i>of our shared archipelagos.</i>

74
00:04:57,380 --> 00:05:00,550
<i>To dismantle these sophisticated</i>
<i>smuggling networks,</i>

75
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:03,428
<i>we must move beyond</i>
<i>the mere ratification of treaties</i>

76
00:05:04,053 --> 00:05:06,556
<i>and focus on the gradual harmonization</i>

77
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:09,267
<i>of end-user certification. In real-time…</i>

78
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,768
[pensive music playing]

79
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:19,610
[reporters clamoring]

80
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:28,453
[clamoring continues]

81
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:31,581
[glass breaking]

82
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:37,295
[tense dramatic music playing]

83
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,409
[music concludes]

84
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:15,166
Sir, they're the members
of Task Force Alpha.

85
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:18,294
They are in charge
of protecting Datu Rahman.

86
00:06:18,795 --> 00:06:23,883
[tense music playing]

87
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:26,636
Agent Marcus Reyes.

88
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:30,098
I have heard a lot about you.

89
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:34,894
I hope you join us
in searching for the truth.

90
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:37,480
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

91
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:41,150
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you too, sir.

92
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:47,115
Agent Eve Castillo, sir.

93
00:06:48,407 --> 00:06:49,242
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

94
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:56,791
Agent Andre Flores.

95
00:06:57,917 --> 00:06:58,876
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

96
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:02,755
[Ryan] Agent Ryan Cruz, sir.

97
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:04,966
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

98
00:07:06,175 --> 00:07:07,760
SPO3 Liam Rodriguez.

99
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:09,762
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

100
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,395
Sabdani.

101
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,398
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

102
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:22,358
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you too, sir.

103
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:25,027
SPO1 Usman Sabdani.

104
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:26,696
Welcome to the NLEA, sir.

105
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:28,906
[in Arabic] As God has willed it.

106
00:07:31,868 --> 00:07:33,453
SPO2 Sean Suarez, sir.

107
00:07:33,536 --> 00:07:34,370
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

108
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:37,039
Agent Domingo, sir.

109
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:38,374
[in English] It's good to meet you.

110
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,001
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

111
00:07:40,084 --> 00:07:41,502
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you too.

112
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:44,338
Head agent, Lara Angeles.

113
00:07:44,422 --> 00:07:46,174
Lara Angeles?

114
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:49,218
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

115
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:52,263
[music intensifies]

116
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:06,068
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you
and the mercy of Allah.

117
00:08:07,403 --> 00:08:08,529
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you too.

118
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,074
[dramatic sting]

119
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,327
‪[dramatic sting]

120
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:17,497
‪[dramatic sting]

121
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:19,665
‪[dramatic sting]

122
00:08:25,713 --> 00:08:27,465
[suspenseful music playing]

123
00:09:10,841 --> 00:09:15,680
I called you here to let you know

124
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:19,392
what our next step is.

125
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:25,565
We are going to stage a public spectacle.

126
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:31,279
We'll make it look like Datu Rahman

127
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:34,240
is surrendering to me.

128
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:40,913
How?

129
00:09:46,502 --> 00:09:47,712
Datu Rahman…

130
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:50,506
you will release a video.

131
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:56,220
In that video, you will recount
what happened to you.

132
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:59,223
You will assert that you are innocent

133
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:01,767
and state how you only fell for a setup.

134
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:07,898
After that, you will challenge
Agent Marcus Reyes

135
00:10:10,234 --> 00:10:16,240
to catch and expose
the people who framed you.

136
00:10:20,202 --> 00:10:21,245
[Jalil] Sir, wait a minute.

137
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:24,749
This might put him in greater danger.

138
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:29,545
Jalil, we have to do this

139
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:36,469
in order to lure out the pests
plaguing NLEA and SID.

140
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:38,262
[tense music playing]

141
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:44,894
If we execute this properly,
we'll be able to smoke them out.

142
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:51,192
Rattle them enough
to get them out of hiding.

143
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:52,610
When that happens…

144
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:58,032
we'll be ready to catch them.

145
00:10:58,824 --> 00:11:00,034
[music intensifies]

146
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:19,345
[tense music playing]

147
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:28,896
- [reporter 1] There they are!
- [reporter 2] Sir! Sir!

148
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:30,981
- [reporter 2] Any comment, sir?
- [officer 1] Move back!

149
00:11:31,065 --> 00:11:32,942
- [reporter 3] Sir, any comment?
- [reporter 4] Over here, sir!

150
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:38,739
- [camera shutters clicking]
- [tense music continues]

151
00:11:48,749 --> 00:11:51,836
- [reporter 5] Sir! Please!
- [officer 2] Move back.

152
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:06,725
Thank you for your service.

153
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:08,811
Be careful, sir.

154
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:10,312
[in Arabic] God willing.

155
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,607
- [reporter 3] Sir, wait!
- [officer 3] Make way.

156
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:15,025
[reporter 3] Please, sir!

157
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:20,406
Until our next meeting.

158
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:22,825
[tense music continues]

159
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,745
[reporter 4] Why did Abubakar surrender?

160
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:28,998
What did you talk about, sir?

161
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:31,417
[car engine starts]

162
00:12:43,804 --> 00:12:46,223
In a surprising turn of events,

163
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:49,810
one of the most wanted personalities
in the country,

164
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:53,272
Datu Rahman Abubakar,
has turned himself in.

165
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:56,233
He is currently under the custody
of the government

166
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,652
after he surrendered directly

167
00:12:58,736 --> 00:13:01,864
to Presidential Chief of Staff
Ahmad Mustapha earlier.

168
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:06,076
Gosh! Things are getting more intense!

169
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,579
[female reporter] Instead of confessing,

170
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:12,291
Abubakar vehemently denied
leading the syndicate

171
00:13:12,374 --> 00:13:15,336
that smuggles illegal arms
into the country.

172
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:20,299
I believe that there are
two sides to every story.

173
00:13:20,382 --> 00:13:24,261
Who are the good guys,
and who are the real villains?

174
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:26,263
Aside from that, Datu Rahman also denied

175
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:30,434
any involvement in the murder
of Vinluan and Condecido

176
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,770
or in the controversial attack

177
00:13:32,853 --> 00:13:36,524
on three then-hospitalized members
of Task Force Alpha.

178
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,235
What else do you want to hear?

179
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:43,239
Datu Rahman has surrendered
and spilled the truth!

180
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:44,573
He is innocent!

181
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:47,993
Come on! It's so easy
to fabricate a story!

182
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:50,037
What if it's all scripted?

183
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:53,249
Would the Presidential
Chief of Staff protect him

184
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,291
if he was a criminal?

185
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:57,294
Why not? No one's totally clean nowadays.

186
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:59,588
Especially when it comes to politics.

187
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:01,715
[in Arabic] Praise be to God!

188
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:05,177
Now that Datu Rahman
is in the right hands,

189
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:08,556
I hope you listen to what he has to say.

190
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:12,601
Stop the baseless accusations
you keep throwing at our people

191
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:16,230
and start listening to our pleas!

192
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:18,649
[sobs] <i>Datu Rahman!</i>

193
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,152
<i>Please tell everyone the whole truth!</i>

194
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:25,239
[in Arabic] <i>God willing!</i>

195
00:14:25,322 --> 00:14:27,950
Given everything that's been going on,

196
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:30,452
what would the Japanese investors think?

197
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:33,247
Investors don't want trouble, do they?

198
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:35,499
Instead of improving our economy,

199
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,376
we're getting into more chaos!

200
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:38,836
Come on, people!

201
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:42,840
<i>According to the Presidential</i>
<i>Chief of Staff Ahmad Mustapha,</i>

202
00:14:42,923 --> 00:14:46,010
<i>if Rahman Abubakar is proven not guilty,</i>

203
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:49,305
<i>the government will consider him</i>
<i>a material witness</i>

204
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,390
<i>who would serve as the key to identifying</i>

205
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:54,727
<i>the real mastermind behind</i>
<i>the crimes that rattled the country.</i>

206
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,353
[tense music playing]

207
00:14:57,813 --> 00:14:58,814
Racquel!

208
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:03,569
[door clicks shut]

209
00:15:05,821 --> 00:15:09,116
We need to execute the plan.

210
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:10,034
Right now.

211
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:12,912
The goods have arrived too, General.

212
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:16,916
Good. Make sure they reach our targets.

213
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,792
I don't want any trouble.

214
00:15:20,127 --> 00:15:21,128
[in English] Noted, General.

215
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:28,969
- [door clicks open and shut]
- [music intensifies]

216
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:35,434
[Rashid] Mister Omar.

217
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,812
How did Datu Rahman end up here?

218
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:41,148
We didn't even know.

219
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:43,609
Since when?

220
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:45,444
He arrived the other night.

221
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:51,367
We're sorry. It's not like
we don't trust you.

222
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,870
It was to ensure Datu Rahman's safety.

223
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:57,498
We didn't want you getting involved

224
00:15:57,581 --> 00:15:59,041
if something bad happened.

225
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:02,836
It's okay, Mister Omar. We understand.

226
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:08,968
But next time, Mister Omar,
don't hesitate to tell us.

227
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:11,845
We are your allies.

228
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:15,724
She's right. We will protect you.

229
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,059
Datu Rahman too.

230
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:18,644
We're ready to help.

231
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:24,316
[sighs]

232
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:29,697
Wait, who brought Datu Rahman here?

233
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:31,657
Was it Jalil?

234
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,492
[gentle music playing]

235
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:38,789
Yes.

236
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:43,794
Thank you, everyone,

237
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:49,174
for always understanding
and protecting us.

238
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:50,759
[exhales]

239
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:54,471
Jalil brought Father here

240
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,974
because he knew he'd be safe here.

241
00:16:58,517 --> 00:16:59,893
Because of you.

242
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:02,104
- [woman sobs]
- [in Tausug] Thank you.

243
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:03,897
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

244
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:05,899
[gentle music playing]

245
00:17:06,483 --> 00:17:10,446
[Norhana chuckles softly, sniffles]

246
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:15,909
[knock on door]

247
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:21,248
Doc, patient Amaro's
lab results have arrived.

248
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:27,087
[sinister music playing]

249
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:33,093
Doc?

250
00:17:34,303 --> 00:17:36,013
Are you okay?

251
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:39,475
I'm fine, Gracia.

252
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:44,646
I'm just worried about Jamilah.
She's been absent for days.

253
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,733
Don't worry, Doc. I'm sure Jamilah's okay.

254
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:49,151
She's probably just taking some time off

255
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:52,738
to avoid getting too much stress.

256
00:17:53,655 --> 00:17:54,740
[sighs deeply]

257
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:58,160
I mean, there's so much
going on in our country.

258
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:02,372
And everyone's talking
about Datu Rahman Abubakar.

259
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:09,046
Hang on, Doc. I just noticed they have
the same last name.

260
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,591
Could they be related?

261
00:18:12,674 --> 00:18:14,510
[pensive music playing]

262
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:15,677
[sighs]

263
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:19,098
Abubakar is a common name.

264
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:21,683
I guess so.

265
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:28,232
I should go. Thanks, Doc.

266
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:29,691
Thank you, Gracia.

267
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:35,239
[door clicks shut]

268
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:39,034
[sighs]

269
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:45,499
Agent Angeles. What do you need?

270
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:48,085
We looked for Datu Rahman for a long time.

271
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:51,672
We looked everywhere for him
yet we couldn't find him.

272
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:54,633
But for you, in an instant, you find him?

273
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:57,553
Ah! No, he turned himself in.

274
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:00,806
It's not in an instant.

275
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:04,643
I spent decades to form a bond
with the Muslim community.

276
00:19:04,726 --> 00:19:07,729
I care about them, and they can feel it.

277
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:08,856
[Lara, in English] Okay…

278
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:11,525
So, if capturing Datu Rahman

279
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:14,736
was such a huge milestone for you,

280
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,363
why did you disappear
when the media arrived?

281
00:19:18,782 --> 00:19:20,450
[sighs, in English] I wonder why.

282
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:21,994
Why?

283
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:24,705
Do I have to pose for the camera?

284
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:29,126
Agent Angeles, I did my job,
and that's good enough for me.

285
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,085
[in English] How humble of you.

286
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:33,088
I'm not humble.
I just know what's important.

287
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:36,091
The media should just be focused
on Marcus.

288
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:39,011
I don't need the masses
to sing me praises.

289
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:41,638
You're hiding something, Espina.

290
00:19:42,806 --> 00:19:44,183
And I'll find it out.

291
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:48,020
[music intensifies]

292
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,152
[Jalil] <i>You're smart, Agent Angeles.</i>

293
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,822
<i>But before you even get</i>
<i>the chance to find out,</i>

294
00:19:58,906 --> 00:20:00,157
<i>my mission will long be completed.</i>

295
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,159
<i>You'll never see me again.</i>

296
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:05,370
[music intensifies, concludes]

297
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:08,916
[tires screech]

298
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:12,252
[breathing heavily]

299
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:16,840
- [screaming]
- [sinister music playing]

300
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:25,307
Madam.

301
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:28,310
Don't you dare touch me! Don't touch me!

302
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:33,565
[screaming]

303
00:20:37,778 --> 00:20:41,865
[Lara breathing heavily]

304
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:53,961
[Manuel] All of this is happening

305
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:57,130
because you lost Datu Rahman.

306
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:03,178
[Manuel] <i>If only you had been more</i>

307
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:06,848
<i>competent from the start,</i>

308
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:10,018
<i>I wouldn't have to go through</i>
<i>all this trouble!</i>

309
00:21:10,102 --> 00:21:12,145
[tense music playing]

310
00:21:21,154 --> 00:21:22,489
[suspenseful sting]

311
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:42,009
[Lara] <i>Before, I only had to spy</i>
<i>on Marcus, but now Espina too?</i>

312
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,885
[in English] I know he's up to no good.

313
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:46,513
[Felix] If he was able to make
Datu Rahman surrender,

314
00:21:46,596 --> 00:21:49,516
do you think he also knows
where Jalil Abubakar is hiding?

315
00:21:50,934 --> 00:21:52,519
There's someone in the upper ranks
on our side.

316
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:53,895
You can't trust anyone
so easily these days.

317
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:57,316
[Marcus] <i>Apart from Azuelo,</i>
<i>you're the only one I fully trust.</i>

318
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:59,901
It's people from the agency
itself doing this.

319
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:03,071
I'll make sure that justice is served.

320
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:04,948
[man] <i>That's where the police officer</i>
<i>wearing glasses</i>

321
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:07,367
<i>picked up Datu Rahman.</i>

322
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:09,369
Jamilah, I'll be gone for a while.

323
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:10,495
Where are you going?

324
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:12,164
I'll return to the island.

325
00:22:12,247 --> 00:22:14,916
[Felix] I won't let them
get away with this.

326
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,668
[knocking on door]

327
00:22:22,549 --> 00:22:24,801
- Your deliveries are all set.
- [in English] Good.

328
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:27,679
[Racquel] <i>Distribute them immediately.</i>

329
00:22:28,305 --> 00:22:31,058
<i>No delays. General is in a rush.</i>
